    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T05:08:11+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T05:08:11+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T18:38:11Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-30T18:38:11Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman sea extends a weak ridge over SA. A trough over central WA extends over southwest SA, and is forecast to move across the west and south later Tuesday, pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. Another high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers west of Coober Pedy, most likely during this afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Coober Pedy. Thunderstorms possibly severe with damaging winds and heavy rain which may lead to flash flooding in the far west during this afternoon and evening. Winds north to northeasterly 25 to 40 km/h shifting south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon and evening. Daytime maximum temperatures 31 to 36.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 4:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 9 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Woomera, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 20 with daytime temperatures reaching 26 to 32.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending east to southeasterly during the morning then tending south to southeasterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 18 with daytime temperatures reaching 27 to 34.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower in the far west, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending east to southeasterly during the morning then tending south to southeasterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 19 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 34.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
